h an ipo on may   the taxus stent was approved in  in europe and other countries and approved in the united states by the fda in march  it was the second drugeluting stent approved in the united states on april   the company acquired longtime competitor guidant for  billion the former guidant was split between bsc and abbott laboratories navilyst medical was formed in february  from boston scientifics fluid management and vascular access business units in october  the company was fined  by the us department of justice for paying a us army doctor to use their devices and recommend them to others companies portal in june  boston scientific officially acquired cameron health for a total sum of  billion paid out incrementally as various revenue milestones were achieved in march  the company announced it would acquire endo international plcs urology business for at least  billion expanding the companys health and prostate treatments lawsuitsedit johnson  johnson lawsuitsedit beginning in  boston scientific and johnson  johnson were involved in a series of litigations involving patents covering heart stent medical devices both parties claimed that the other had infringed upon their patents the litigation was settled once boston scientific agreed to pay  million to johnson  johnson in september  and an additional  billion in february  it was announced in november  that johnson  johnson would have another chance for payback after a multibillion dollar trial was set for  november  a new york federal court judge would hear the case without a jury to decide whether boston scientific should be held liable for the contract breach restatementedit on nov  boston scientific restated its financial results for  as well as its quarterly results for the first three quarters of  due to the occurrence of business irregularities in the operations of its japanese subsidiary profitsedit profits rose to € million in  in the irishbased plant in  the profits were € million profits increased by