able for offering a minimally invasive implantable cardioverterdefibrillator icd which they call the emblem subcutaneous implantable defibrillator sicd contents  history  lawsuits  johnson  johnson lawsuits  restatement  profits  notes  external links historyedit boston scientific was formed june   as a holding company for a medical products company called meditech and to position the company for growth in interventional medicine the company went public through an ipo on may   the taxus stent was approved in  in europe and other countries and approved in the united states by the fda in march  it was the second drugeluting stent approved in the united states on april   the company acquired longtime competitor guidant for  billion the former guidant was split between bsc and abbott laboratories navilyst medical was formed in february  from boston scientifics fluid management and vascular access business units in october  the company was fined  by the us department of justice for paying a us army doctor to use their devices and recommend them to others companies portal in june  boston scientific officially acquired cameron health for a total sum of  billion paid out incrementally as various revenue milestones were achieved in march  the company announced it would acquire endo international plcs urology business for at least  billion expanding the companys health and prostate treatments lawsuitsedit johnson  johnson lawsuitsedit beginning in  boston scientific and johnson  johnson were involved in a series of litigations involving patents covering heart stent medical devices both parties claimed that the other had infringed upon their patents the litigation was settled once boston scientific agreed to pay  million to johnson  johnson in september  and an additional  billion in february  it was announced in november  that johnson  johnson would have another chance for payback after a multibillion dollar trial was set for  november  a new york federal court judge would hear the case without a jury to decide whether boston scientific should be held liable for the contract breach restatementedit on nov  boston scientific restated its financial results for  as well as its quarterly results for the first three quarters of  due to the occurrence of business irregularities in the operations of its japanese subsidiary profitsedit profits rose to € million in  in the irishbased plant in  the profits were € million profits increased by  in one year notesedit  httpwwwbostonheraldcombusinessbusinessmarketsceomahoneytobechairmanofbostonscientific  a b c d boston scientific  annual report pdf   a b shelley wood  mar  fda approves taxus paclitaxeleluting stent wwwmedscapecom retrieved  feb    a b boston scientific closes cameron health acquisition pr newswire ubm plc  june  retrieved  february    emblem sicd system boston scientific archived from the original on  february  retrieved  february    a b about us  history wwwbostonscientificcomenusaboutushistory retrieved  feb    guidant battle ends in favor of boston scientific associated press january   retrieved    boston scientific completes combination with guidant april   archived from the original on april   retrieved   boston scientifics press release on the acquisition  boston scientific spinoff aiming to tap veins without causing infections august   retrieved    bernton hal army whistleblower fights to clear name seattle times  august  p   mclaughlin kim march   boston scientific buys endo mens health unit for  billion bloomberg   boston scientific to pay jj b to settle stent patent disputes the wall street journal february    jj seeks over  billion in damages from boston scientific at trial reuters  november   boston scientific addresses japan business irregularities   irish subsidiary of boston scientific sees profits jump the irish times retrieved   external linksedit boston scientific official web site business data for boston scientific google finance yahoo finance reuters sec filings b